Liam's User stories


1. Smart Journey Planning (Features 1, 3, 4)


User story:

"As a UCD student living in Portobello, I want to see real-time weather and 30-minute occupancy predictions so that I can decide whether to cycle or take the bus to my 9 AM lecture."



Acceptance criteria:

Check Live Weather

Given the user is on the Home screen,

When the system detects the location as Dublin,

Then the system displays real-time temperature, rain probability, and cycling alerts.

Predict Future Availability

Given the user is on the interactive map,

When the user selects a specific station and clicks "30-min Prediction",

Then the system displays the predicted number of bikes and stands based on ML patterns.




2. Active Rental Tracking (Feature 10)


User story:

"As a budget-conscious student, I want to track my current rental duration in real-time so that I can return the bike within the 30-minute free period to avoid extra charges."



Acceptance criteria:

Start Live Timer

Given a bike has been successfully unlocked,

When the rental session begins,

Then the system displays a dynamic timer on the main interface tracking minutes used.

Estimate Surcharge

Given the user is currently on an active ride,

When the rental duration exceeds 30 minutes,

Then the system automatically calculates and displays the current estimated rental cost.




3. Account & Subscription Management (Features 5, 6)


User story:

"As a heavy user, I want to manage my Annual Subscription and top-up my account credit via my login so that my daily commute is never interrupted by payment issues."



Acceptance criteria:

Manage Subscription Plans

Given the user has logged into their account,

When the user navigates to the "Subscriptions" section,

Then the system displays options to choose or renew Daily, Monthly, or Annual plans.

Top-up Account Credit

Given the user is in the payment settings,

When the user inputs an amount and confirms payment,

Then the system updates the account balance and displays a success message.



4. Interactive Navigation & Support (Features 2, 7)



User story:

"As a commuter traveling to different work locations, I want to see precise station info and access 'How-to' guides so that I can find docks that support credit card payments and return bikes correctly."



Acceptance criteria:

Filter Station Services

Given the user is viewing the interactive map,

When the user taps on a specific station marker,

Then the system displays a popup with the station name, distance, and available services (e.g., Credit Card terminal).

Access Instructional Guide

Given the user needs help with the rental process,

When the user selects the "How to" option from the menu,

Then the system displays step-by-step visual instructions for renting and returning bikes.



5. Local Engagement (Features 8, 9)


User story:

"As a Dublin resident, I want to access local news and special student offers so that I can stay informed about city events and save money on cycling-related costs."



Acceptance criteria:

View Dublin Updates

Given the user is on the main app dashboard,

When the user navigates to "Dublin News",

Then the system displays a feed of local news and traffic alerts.

Claim Special Offers

Given the user is in the "Special Offer" section,

When the user selects a student-specific discount,

Then the system provides the redemption details and applies the offer to the user's profile.
